snippet.textDisplay:
Loved kobe, he was a scoring machine. Kd said it himself on the show hot ones, when asked what did you learn the most from kobe. Kd said "everytime you touch the ball, shoot it" LOL. People can say ballhog, shoots too much etc etc. To me, i loved watching him be a gunner and str8 killer. Loved watching him score and go on scoring streaks of 40-50+. If kobe wasnt the one shooting, i didnt care. Sometimes he took difficult shots, made alot of them. Sometimes shot over a double or even triple team ffs haha. Ill never forget the feeling i had everytime the game was on the line and he made incredible clutch shots other guys either wouldnt take or couldnt make. He was the most cutthroat coldblooded basketball player ive ever seen and the mentality, pain threshold, able to play with injuries any other player would be sidelined for- to the extreme work ethic and determination to give it everything every night out there on the floor.

When he retired, he was asked do you have any regrets or was it hard to walk away from the game. He simply said absolutely not, its because i gave everything i had to the game of basketball....everything! I left nothing out there on the court.

R.i.p kobe bean bryant. To me, the greatest of all time and always my favorite basketball legend ever.

#mamba4ever #kb24 #kb8 #gigi #GOAT

snippet.textDisplay:
To Vanessa Bryant and her remaining Children, Wife and Mother, Children and Siblings of the late Kobe Bryant and Gianna Bryant:

I am deeply sorry for your terrible loss and don’t quite know how or if I will be able to comfort you during your time of grief, nevertheless I must try. You mustn’t worry about what other’s think or say during this terrible time in your lives, but only what it’ll take to get you through this day and everyday going forward.

I know that at this moment nothing in life seems to make any sense, and more than likely this tragedy has nearly driven you insane.

I just wanted to let you all know that you are not alone in dealing with your grief, and that I also share your pain.

While grieving the loss of your loved ones it’s not unusual to get angry and/or bitter when you look to our Lord and ask him WHY!

But through personal experiences, I can attest to the fact that He will be there to comfort you throughout your lives and wipe each teardrop whenever you begin to cry.

Please do not ever lose your faith in Him as I once did, only to find that you truly have nowhere else to turn accept for to Him,

Because other’s can only offer you temporary relief if any, so try hard not to find yourselves seeking your necessity for comfort, only in them.

It won’t be easy for any of you to go on each day without them and your lives will never be the same,

And there is nothing that’ll provide you with the comfort you so desperately need right now, no amount of attention, riches or fame.

I pray for you all day and night and that God will soothe your aching heart’s,

And that this terrible tragedy will not prevent you from trusting in God or somehow tear you apart.

Blessings, peace, comfort and love to you and your family today and always.
Elizabeth (Liz) Williams-Ngom
written to you from:
West Africa, Dakar Senegal 🇸🇳
Citizen of the United States of America 🇺🇸
January 27, 2020
